< review>
This place was so fun and so special. We started on the outdoor patio, which had lots of warm heaters! But it started to rain and they kindly accommodated reseating us inside (really appreciated it!!). We had the artichoke appetizer and we both got the burger - both of which were really good. The service was good and we really enjoyed our dinner! On top of that, there was live music - piano and a singer! It was so beautiful! Such a treat, we will be back!</review>

Frank S (Bobddog)< /Name>
<time>1554359105924<//time><rating>5< /rating><text>Located in the historic Cypress Inn Hotel in Downtown Carmel.  Terry's Lounge is named after Doris Day's son, whom I had the pleasure of meeting multiple times before his passing. This is a well maintained upscale hotel from around the 1930's.  I have been frequenting this bar for many years with my immediate family, pets and close friends.  The hotel is completely dog friendly along with the Terry's Lounge. Bring your well behaved pup(s) for a expertly crafted cocktail, enjoy the nice upscale bar menu while watching the hotel guests, thier children and fur babies returing from a day in Downtown Carmel. Introverts beware, because when you're at Terry's Lounge you will always end up in friendly conversations with strangers about their travels and their dogs.  Always friendly attentive staff, excellent quality food for lunch and dinner on the menu with beautiful "Moorish Casbah Chique"  surroundings.  Bonus: Doris Day memorabilia is tastefully displayed throughout the bar.< /text><pics>None<//pics>< resp>

<Response>{'time': 1470179432783, 'text': 'Thanks Calvin for the review we hope to see you and the kids again!'}<//Response><Review>You don't find too many quick service Indian places, so when I saw this place I knew I had to try it.

The atmosphere is a typical family run style place.  Ambiance is basically a fast food joint versus "restaurant".

The food is excellent.  We ordered, Chicken Tikka Masala, Hakka Noodles with Chicken and Naan.  The Chicken Tikka Masala was excellent with the naan and rice.  My kids absolutely loved the Hakka Noodles.  It was very flavorful and the chicken had a nice light crunch to it.

Typically, Indian food is expensive for the portion sizes.  At Wok N Tandoor, the price point is lower than traditional Indian restaurants and in my opinion the service size is larger... a big plus!  If you haven't tried this place, I definitely recommend it!<//Review><rate>4</rate></record>

We got to go here for the first time and it was a great birthday party we attended.  My daughter had a great time playing in the park the reason why I gave it a four stars is because the park needs a lot of work it is not the cleanest and the grass area had lots of patches and uneven dirt areas! There is a lot of bums that hang out around here too so you have to watch your child very closely it is not a part or you can stop watching your kids and let them play.  I was very nervous with my daughter even though she is older.  But once she started playing with all the other kids I felt better that they stayed together and I got to play with them too and I had a great time.  I would go back to this park just be careful;  I heard that the lake is contaminated so if your ball goes in the lake I leave it there!</Text>

On the other hand during the loan process the new lender had to reach out to S & R insurance more than once for information on our home owners insurance policy. It is during these times Mr Fabian Serrano, Business Operations Mngr. responded to the requests on both occasions in a very efficient and speedy manner.
